cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.MS 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a parallelization method for the stochastic dual coordinate descent algorithm, which is commonly used in solving machine learning problems such as linear SVM and logistic regression. It also discusses the convergence properties of the proposed algorithm, which is a common topic in machine learning research. 

It may also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it focuses on parallelization and asynchronous algorithms. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper discusses the coordinate descent algorithm and its variants. 

cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.MS (Mathematical Software) are also possible categories as the paper involves analyzing the convergence properties of the algorithm and implementing it efficiently.
